### Core Modules

#### [NEW] [types.ts](file:///Users/phucdinh/data/Projects/vibecoding/openclaw-skills/facebook-group-monitor-pattern/scripts/src/config/types.ts)

TypeScript interfaces for the entire config and data model:
- `MonitorConfig`, `GroupConfig`, `Settings`
- `ScrapedPost`, `MatchedPost`
- `MatchMode: "word" | "contains" | "regex"`

#### [NEW] [loader.ts](file:///Users/phucdinh/data/Projects/vibecoding/openclaw-skills/facebook-group-monitor-pattern/scripts/src/config/loader.ts)

- Parse `config.yaml` using `js-yaml`
- Validate required fields
- Resolve relative paths (browser data dir)

#### [NEW] [pattern-matcher.ts](file:///Users/phucdinh/data/Projects/vibecoding/openclaw-skills/facebook-group-monitor-pattern/scripts/src/matcher/pattern-matcher.ts)

Three match modes:
- **`word`**: Exact word boundary `\bPATTERN\b` (for stock tickers like FPT, VNM)
- **`contains`**: Split pattern into words, check ALL exist in text (case-insensitive). `"DevOPS remote"` → checks both `devops` AND `remote` are in text
- **`regex`**: User-provided regex evaluated directly

Returns `{ matched: boolean, matchedPatterns: string[] }`.

#### [NEW] [browser.ts](file:///Users/phucdinh/data/Projects/vibecoding/openclaw-skills/facebook-group-monitor-pattern/scripts/src/crawler/browser.ts)

Playwright stealth browser setup:
- Same `user_agent`, `BROWSER_ARGS`, stealth plugin as Python version
- **Separate** persistent browser data at `scripts/.browser-data/` (requires its own login)
- Uses `playwright-extra` + `puppeteer-extra-plugin-stealth` for Node.js stealth

#### [NEW] [scraper.ts](file:///Users/phucdinh/data/Projects/vibecoding/openclaw-skills/facebook-group-monitor-pattern/scripts/src/crawler/scraper.ts)

Port of the Python scraper to TypeScript:
- Navigate to group → scroll with random delays → extract posts via JS `evaluate`
- Extract: `author`, [text](file:///Users/phucdinh/data/Projects/vibecoding/openclaw-skills/facebook-group-monitor/scripts/fb-group-monitor.py#226-248), `url`, `images`, `total_comment`, `total_liked`, `total_shared`
- Post URL extraction uses same 4-pass strategy as existing Python skill
- **No screenshots** (per requirement)
- **Engagement metrics**: extract numbers from visible text like `"12 comments"` → `12`, `"5 likes"` → `5`. Returns `null` if text not found

#### [NEW] [rate-limiter.ts](file:///Users/phucdinh/data/Projects/vibecoding/openclaw-skills/facebook-group-monitor-pattern/scripts/src/crawler/rate-limiter.ts)

Anti-detection strategy for ~10 groups:
- Random delay between page actions: 3-8 seconds
- Cooldown between groups: 2-5 minutes (randomized)
- Random scroll speed variation
- Human-like mouse movement simulation (optional)
- Max groups per session: configurable (default 5), then restart browser context

#### [NEW] [date-parser.ts](file:///Users/phucdinh/data/Projects/vibecoding/openclaw-skills/facebook-group-monitor-pattern/scripts/src/crawler/date-parser.ts)

Parse relative time text (Option A):
- Vietnamese: `"Hôm qua"`, `"2 giờ"`, `"1 ngày"`, `"3 phút"`
- English: `"Yesterday"`, `"2h"`, `"1d"`, `"3m"`
- Returns estimated `Date` object
- Function `isYesterday(text: string): boolean` for filtering

#### [NEW] [models.ts](file:///Users/phucdinh/data/Projects/vibecoding/openclaw-skills/facebook-group-monitor-pattern/scripts/src/storage/models.ts)

Mongoose schemas:
```typescript
// MatchedPost schema
{
  monitor_name: String,       // "VN30 Stock Tracker"
  group_url: String,
  group_name: String,
  post_url: String,           // unique index
  author: String,
  text: String,
  matched_patterns: [String], // ["FPT", "VCB"]
  total_comment: Number | null,
  total_liked: Number | null,
  total_shared: Number | null,
  post_date: String,          // "2026-03-15" (estimated from relative time)
  scraped_at: Date,
  images: Number
}
```

#### [NEW] [dedup.ts](file:///Users/phucdinh/data/Projects/vibecoding/openclaw-skills/facebook-group-monitor-pattern/scripts/src/storage/dedup.ts)

See [Dedup Daily Auto-Clean](#dedup-daily-auto-clean--how-it-works) section above for full explanation.

#### [NEW] [connection.ts](file:///Users/phucdinh/data/Projects/vibecoding/openclaw-skills/facebook-group-monitor-pattern/scripts/src/storage/connection.ts)

- Load `MONGODB_URI` from `.env` via `dotenv`
- Mongoose connect with retry logic
- Graceful disconnect on process exit

#### [NEW] [index.ts](file:///Users/phucdinh/data/Projects/vibecoding/openclaw-skills/facebook-group-monitor-pattern/scripts/src/index.ts)

CLI entry point with commands:
- `scrape <monitor_name>` — run a specific monitor
- `scrape-all` — run all monitors sequentially with cooldowns
- `list` — list all configured monitors
- [status](file:///Users/phucdinh/data/Projects/vibecoding/openclaw-skills/facebook-group-monitor/scripts/fb-group-monitor.py#362-390) — check browser session + MongoDB connection
- `clean-dedup` — manually clean dedup tracking

Output: JSON to stdout (same format as existing Python skill, plus `matched_patterns`).

#### [NEW] [fb-monitor-pattern.sh](file:///Users/phucdinh/data/Projects/vibecoding/openclaw-skills/facebook-group-monitor-pattern/scripts/fb-monitor-pattern.sh)

Shell wrapper that:
1. Checks for Node.js
2. Runs `npx tsx src/index.ts` (using `tsx` for TypeScript execution, no build step)
3. Passes all arguments through

